Revision history for RPi-ADC-MCP3008

3.1802 UNREL
    - Added DEVICE SPECIFICS and ON THE WIRE sections to the POD's TECHNICAL
      DATA: chip capability summary, wiring map, and the full-duplex 3-byte
      SPI frame diagrammed byte-by-byte, verified against the MCP3004/3008
      datasheet (DS21295D)
    - Removed the XS layer entirely; the module is now pure Perl, with all
      SPI transport delegated to RPi::SPI
    - GPIO CS mode (channel above 1) no longer strobes the hardware CE0 pin
      alongside the chosen GPIO on every transfer, via RPi::SPI 3.1802's
      per-transaction SPI_NO_CS handling
    - Added full bit-bang support: pass new() a hashref of RPi::SPI bit-bang
      params to run the ADC on arbitrary GPIO pins
    - Object destruction now parks the CS pin deselected (HIGH) and driven,
      instead of selecting the chip then floating the pin
    - raw() and percent() now croak on a missing or non-integer ADC input
      channel
    - POD: corrected the "bit-bang" description of GPIO CS mode, documented
      the new true bit-bang mode with datasheet-derived delay guidance
    - Regenerated README from the current POD
    - Prereqs: RPi::SPI 3.1802 replaces the direct RPi::Const and
      WiringPi::API requirements
    - Added a DATASHEET POD section pointing to the bundled
      docs/datasheet/MCP3008.pdf; repointed the inline datasheet link off
      its github.io URL
    - POD: corrected the DESCRIPTION's device-compatibility claim - the
      MCP3004 shares the MCP3008 control word (D2 a "don't care") and works
      unchanged, but the MCP3002 uses a different control word (SGL/DIFF,
      ODD/SIGN, MSBF) and clocks its result out sooner, so this module's
      fixed 3-byte frame is not compatible with it; verified against
      DS21294E and DS21295D

3.1801    2026-06-12
        - Migrated constants from removed RPi::WiringPi::Constant to
          RPi::Const (incl. Makefile.PL prereq)
        - Replaced wpi_setup()/spi_setup() with wiringPiSetupGpio()/
          wiringPiSPISetup() for WiringPi::API 3.18; aligns Perl-level
          setup with the XS (GPIO numbering) and fixes the undefined
          spi_setup() under the :wiringPi-only import

2.3605  2019-11-18
        - modified what we send in to SPI setup. A recent change in WiringPi
          broke sending in the GPIO pin as a channel
        - updated POD coverage tests

2.3604  2017-06-28
        - added git info to Makefile.PL
        - bumped prereq of WiringPi::API to 2.3612
        - bump prereq of RPi::WiringPi::Constant to 1.00

2.36.3  2016-03-13
        - removed unnecessary C includes
        - changed version numbering scheme from 2.36.x to 2.360x

2.36.2  2017-03-11
        - changed percent return to a 2 digit float from an int, perl the
          documentation
        - added Fritzing docs and the datasheet
        - updated POD

2.36.1  2017-03-11
        - initial release
